---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
const signals = await getCollection('signals');
---
<BaseLayout title="SIGNALS — SECTOR 404" description="Private transmission channels, infected audio, collaborator artifacts and signals you were not cleared to receive.">
  <section class="hero small portal page-hero signal-hero">
    <div class="breach-frame" aria-hidden="true">
      <span>SIGNAL/CARRIER-001</span>
      <span>RITUAL FEED UNSTABLE</span>
      <span>CHOIR TRACE ACTIVE</span>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="terminal-label">Unlisted transmission channel</p>
      <h1 data-text="SIGNALS">SIGNALS</h1>
      <p class="lead">This is where sound arrives before it becomes public. Bands, collaborators, cards and objects pass through as infected transmissions. PRIEST is the first one that refused to stay contained.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="status-strip" aria-label="Signal status">
    <div><span>First breach</span><strong>PRIEST</strong></div>
    <div><span>Carrier</span><strong>Audio / cards / artifacts</strong></div>
    <div><span>Ritual state</span><strong>Neon Rite Noir</strong></div>
    <div><span>Clearance</span><strong>Not requested</strong></div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div>
        <p class="kicker">Signal files</p>
        <h2>Do not treat these as announcements.</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="muted">Each Signal is a case record opened too early: part music, part artifact, part thing listening back.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid wide">
      {signals.map((signal, index) => (
        <article class="card" data-code={`SIG_${String(index + 1).padStart(3, '0')}`}>
          <span class="kicker">{signal.data.status} / {signal.data.type}</span>
          <h2>{signal.data.title}</h2>
          <p class="muted">{signal.data.summary}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section portal-grid">
    <article class="panel">
      <p class="kicker">First exposed packet</p>
      <h2>PRIEST: FIRST TRANSMISSION</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-top:1rem">A compact series of evidence from the stage, the temple and the machine. It feels like merch only if you ignore the blood in the file.</p>
      <div class="manifest-list">
        <div class="manifest-item"><span>000</span><b>THE SIGNAL</b><span>origin</span></div>
        <div class="manifest-item"><span>001</span><b>MERCURY</b><span>vox-priest</span></div>
        <div class="manifest-item"><span>002</span><b>DISCO GIRL</b><span>altar</span></div>
        <div class="manifest-item"><span>003</span><b>ECHO</b><span>witness</span></div>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="panel copy-block signal-skin-panel">
      <p class="kicker">Neon Rite Noir</p>
      <p>The stage becomes a temple because the system needs bodies to carry sound. The audience becomes a choir because repetition is easier to smuggle than doctrine.</p>
      <p class="rule">Mercury is signal. Disco Girl is the body ritual. ECHO is the witness standing close enough to the poison to deliver it further.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section signal-ritual">
    <div class="ritual-ring" aria-hidden="true"><span>Hg</span><span>NaCl</span><span>S</span></div>
    <article class="panel copy-block">
      <p class="kicker">Liturgical contamination</p>
      <h2>The audio is not the dangerous part.</h2>
      <p>The signal enters through performance, sleeves, collector cards, bootleg objects and repeated symbols. By the time it becomes music, it has already chosen a body.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section portal-grid media-vein">
    <article class="panel copy-block surface-card surface-biometric">
      <p class="kicker">Recovered carrier</p>
      <h2>Sometimes the channel returns residue instead of a file.</h2>
      <p>Not portraiture. Not a visual hook. A damaged surface left behind after the signal moved through something living.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="panel copy-block surface-card surface-shrine">
      <p class="kicker">Signal remains</p>
      <h2>The infection should feel discovered, not promoted.</h2>
      <p>PRIEST appears through fragments, ritual geometry and corrupted archive texture. If it starts looking like a campaign, the containment has already won.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
